        <p>
            Henry is currently the youngest living bear at the Habitat. He was born in captivity on May 9, 2013 in Australia. After turning two, his mother started pushing him away and he moved to the Habitat in 2015. Henry is considered a sub-adult male. This means he’s technically not a cub anymore but he isn’t a full blown adult. Henry enjoys spending time with Ganuk and Inukshuk and will commonly be seen sparring with them.
